<example id="fs-id1168345450032">
<exercise id="fs-id1168345426577"><problem id="fs-id1168345384368">
<para id="fs-id1168345215986">The perimeter of a triangular garden is 24 feet. The lengths of two sides are four feet and nine feet. How long is the third side?</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-id1168345217762">
<title>Solution</title>

<table id="eip-id1167269951399" class="unnumbered unstyled" summary="We are given a table with directions on the left and mathematical steps on the right. Step 1. Read the problem. Draw the figure and label it with the given information. To the right of this, we have a triangle with side lengths 9 ft, 4 ft, and c. Below this, it is noted that P equals 24 ft. Step 2. Identify what you are looking for. To the right of this, we have the length of the third side of a triangle. Step 3. Name. Choose a variable to represent it. To the right of this, we have let c equal the third side. Step 4. Translate. Write the appropriate formula and substitute. To the right of this, we have P = a plus b plus c. We are told to substitute in the given information. To the right of this, we have 24 ft equals 4 ft plus 9 ft plus c. Step 5. Solve the equation. To the right of this, we have 24 equals 13 plus c. Below this, we have 11 equals c. Step 6. Check. Under this we have 24 equals with a question mark over it 4 plus 9 plus 11. Below this, 24 equals 24 with a check mark next to it. Step 7. Answer the question: The third side is 11 feet long"><label/><tgroup cols="3">

<tbody>

<row>
   <entry><emphasis>Step 1. Read </emphasis> the problem. Draw the figure and label it with the given information.</entry>
   <entry><media id="eip-id116723422342340" alt="."><image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/CNX_ElemAlg_Figure_03_04_004a_img_new.jpg"/></media><newline/><media id="eip-id11672342220" alt="."><image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/CNX_ElemAlg_Figure_03_04_004b_img_new.jpg"/></media></entry>
 </row>

<row>
   <entry><emphasis>Step 2. Identify </emphasis> what you are looking for.</entry>
   <entry>length of the third side of a triangle</entry>
 </row>
  <row>
   <entry><emphasis>Step 3. Name. </emphasis> Choose a variable to represent it.</entry>
   <entry>Let <m:math><m:mi>c</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo></m:math> the third side.</entry>
 </row>
 <row>
   <entry><emphasis>Step 4. Translate. </emphasis></entry>
   <entry/>
 </row>
 <row>
   <entry>Write the appropriate formula and substitute.</entry>
   <entry><media id="eip-id1167234223429384209384" alt="."><image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/CNX_ElemAlg_Figure_03_04_004c_img_new.jpg"/></media></entry>
 </row>
 <row>
   <entry>Substitute in the given information.</entry>
   <entry><media id="eip-id116723422344209384" alt="."><image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/CNX_ElemAlg_Figure_03_04_004d_img_new.jpg"/></media></entry>
