<para id="fs-id1168345203472">The triangle properties we used so far apply to all triangles. Now we will look at one specific type of triangle—a right triangle. A <term class="no-emphasis" id="term-00004">right triangle</term> has one <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>90</m:mn><m:mtext>°</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math> angle, which we usually mark with a small square in the corner.</para>
