<example id="fs-id1168345342358">
<exercise id="fs-id1168345342360">
<problem id="fs-id1168345375209">
<para id="fs-id1168345375211">Use the Pythagorean Theorem to find the length of the leg shown below.</para>
<media id="fs-id1168345376483" alt="A right angle with one leg marked 5. The hypotenuse is labeled 13.">
<image mime-type="image/jpeg" src="../../media/CNX_ElemAlg_Figure_03_04_015_img_new.jpg"/>
</media>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-id1168345453021">
<title>Solution</title>
<para id="fs-id1168345405688"><table id="eip-id1167265594940" class="unnumbered unstyled can-break" summary="We are given a table with directions on the left and mathematical steps on the right. Step 1. Read the problem. We have a right triangle with legs labeled 5 and b and hypotenuse labeled 13. Step 2. Identify what you are looking for. To the right of this, we have the length of the leg of the triangle. Step 3. Name. Choose a variable to represent it. To the right of this, we have let b equal the length of the other leg in the triangle. Step 4. Translate. Write the appropriate formula and substitute. To the right of this, we have a squared plus b squared equals c squared. Below this, we have 5 squared plus b squared equals 13 squared. Step 5. Solve the equation. Isolate the variable term. Use the definition of square root. Simplify. To the right of this, we have 25 plus b squared equals 169. Below this, we have b squared equals 144. Below this, b equals the square root of 144. Below this, b equals 12. Step 6. Check. Under this we have 5 squared plus 12 squared equals with a question mark over it 13 squared, below which we have 25 plus 144 equals with a question mark over it 169. Below this, 169 equals 169 with a check mark next to it. Step 7. Answer the question: The length of the leg is 12."><label/><tgroup cols="3">
<tbody>

<row>
   <entry><emphasis>Step 1. Read </emphasis> the problem. </entry>
   <entry/>
   <entry/>
 </row>

<row>
   <entry><emphasis>Step 2. Identify </emphasis> what you are looking for.</entry>
   <entry/>
   <entry>the length of the leg of the triangle</entry>
 </row>
  <row>
   <entry><emphasis>Step 3. Name.</emphasis> Choose a variable to represent it.</entry>
   <entry/>
   <entry>Let <emphasis effect="italics">b</emphasis> = the leg of the triangle.</entry>
 </row>
  <row>
   <entry>Lable side <emphasis effect="italics">b</emphasis>.</entry>
   <entry/>
   <entry><media id="eip-id1167263182489" alt="."><image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/CNX_ElemAlg_Figure_03_04_016b_img_new.jpg"/></media></entry>
 </row>
 <row>
   <entry><emphasis>Step 4. Translate</emphasis></entry>
   <entry/>
   <entry/>
 </row>

 <row>
   <entry>Write the appropriate formula.</entry>
   <entry/>
   <entry><m:math><m:msup><m:mi>a</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:msup><m:mi>b</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:msup><m:mi>c</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup></m:math></entry>
 </row>
 <row>
   <entry>Substitute.</entry>
   <entry/>
   <entry><m:math><m:msup><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:msup><m:mi>b</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:msup><m:mn>13</m:mn><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup></m:math></entry>
 </row>
 <row>
   <entry><emphasis>Step 5. Solve </emphasis>the equation.</entry>
   <entry/>
   <entry><m:math><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:msup><m:mi>b</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>169</m:mn></m:math></entry>
 </row>
 <row>
   <entry>Isolate the variable term.</entry>
   <entry/>
   <entry><m:math><m:mspace width="2.1em"/><m:msup><m:mi>b</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>144</m:mn></m:math></entry>
 </row>
 <row>
   <entry>Use the definition of square root.</entry>
   <entry/>
   <entry><m:math><m:mspace width="2.1em"/><m:msup><m:mi>b</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:msqrt><m:mn>144</m:mn></m:msqrt></m:math></entry>
 </row>
 <row>
   <entry>Simplify.</entry>
   <entry/>
   <entry><m:math><m:mspace width="2.6em"/><m:mi>b</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>12</m:mn></m:math></entry>
 </row>
 <row>
   <entry><emphasis>Step 6. Check. </emphasis><newline/><newline/><media id="eip-id1167265973164" alt="."><image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/CNX_ElemAlg_Figure_03_04_016a_img_new.jpg"/></media></entry>
   <entry/>
   <entry/>
 </row>
  <row>
   <entry> <emphasis>Step 7. Answer </emphasis>the question.</entry>
   <entry/>
   <entry>The length of the leg is 12.</entry>
 </row>
 </tbody>



</tgroup>
</table></para></solution>
</exercise>
</example>
