<para id="fs-id1168345420686"><table id="eip-id1167271174266" class="unnumbered unstyled can-break" summary="We are given a table with directions on the left and mathematical steps on the right. Step 1. Read the problem. Step 2. Identify what you are looking for. To the right of this, we have the length and width. Step 3. Name. Choose a variable to represent it. To the right of this, we have let w equal the width. The length is four more than twice the width; hence, we let 2w plus 4 equal the length. Below this, we have a rectangle with length 2w plus 4 and width w. Below this, we have P equals 32 cm. Step 4. Translate. Write the appropriate formula and substitute in the given information. To the right of this, we have P equals 2L plus 2W. Below this, we have 32 equals 2 times the quantity (2w plus 4) plus 2w. Step 5. Solve the equation. To the right of this, we have 32 equals 4w plus 8 plus 2w. Below this, we have 32 equals 6w plus 8. Below this, 24 equals 6w. Below this 4 equals w. Below this the length is determined: 2w plus 4, so 2 times 4 plus 4 equals 12. The length is 12 cm. Step 6. Check. We have a rectangle with length 12 cm and width 4 cm. Below this, we have P equals 2L plus 2W. Below this we have 32 equals with a question mark over it 2 times 12 plus 2 times 4. Below this, we have 32 equals 32. Step 7. Answer the question: The length is 12 cm, and the width is 4 cm.">
