<section id="fs-id1168345386602" class="everyday">
<title>Everyday Math</title>
<exercise id="fs-id1168345386607">
<problem id="fs-id1168345386609">
<para id="fs-id1168345426541">Christa wants to put a fence around her triangular flowerbed. The sides of the flowerbed are six feet, eight feet and 10 feet. How many feet of fencing will she need to enclose her flowerbed?</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-id1168345426547">
<para id="fs-id1168345426549">240 feet</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-id1168345426554">
<problem id="fs-id1168345408329">
<para id="fs-id1168345408331">Jose just removed the children’s playset from his back yard to make room for a rectangular garden. He wants to put a fence around the garden to keep out the dog. He has a 50 foot roll of fence in his garage that he plans to use. To fit in the backyard, the width of the garden must be 10 feet. How long can he make the other length?</para>
</problem>
